        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 18 at 3:52PM CDT until August 18 at 4:45PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Wheeler County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Hemphill County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 445 PM CDT.

* At 351 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Briscoe, or
23 miles east of Miami, and is nearly stationary.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

* Locations impacted include...
Briscoe, Wheeler, and Allison.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
